-- Saudi Equity Movers: Bank Albilad, Saudi Arabian Amiantit
-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 2012-02-04T14:22:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-04/saudi-equity-movers-bank-albilad-saudi-arabian-amiantit.html
The  Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  rose for
a ninth day, gaining 1.1 percent to 6,733.68, at the 3:30 p.m.
close in Riyadh.  The following stocks were active in Saudi Arabia’s market.  Saudi Arabian Amiantit Co. (SAAC)   reached the highest
close since July 2, gaining 2.2 percent to 18.40 riyals. The
construction materials manufacturer said its board recommended
distributing a dividend of 1.25 riyals a share for 2011.  Bank Albilad (ALBI AB) jumped 6.7 percent, the largest
increase since May, to 24 riyals. Saudi Arabia’s second-smallest
lender by market value signed a deal with the government to
accelerate home lending, al-Sharq al-Awsat reported on Feb. 2,
citing a signing ceremony.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in  Riyadh  at 
